{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:ephesians.3",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "ephesians",
    "chapterNumber": 3,
    "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3",
    "summary": "Source text for Ephesians 3 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.3.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:1",
      "text": "For this reason I, Paul, a prisoner for Christ Jesus on behalf of you Gentiles—",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.3.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:2",
      "text": "assuming that you have heard of the stewardship of God's grace that was given to me for you,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.3.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:3",
      "text": "how the mystery was made known to me by revelation, as I have written briefly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.3.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:4",
      "text": "When you read this you can perceive my insight into the mystery of Christ,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.3.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:5",
      "text": "which was not made known to the sons of men in other generations as it has now been revealed to his holy apostles and prophets by the Spirit;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.3.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:6",
      "text": "that is, how the Gentiles are fellow heirs, members of the same body, and partakers of the promise in Christ Jesus through the gospel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.3.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:7",
      "text": "Of this gospel I was made a minister according to the gift of God's grace which was given me by the working of his power.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.3.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:8",
      "text": "To me, though I am the very least of all the saints, this grace was given, to preach to the Gentiles the unsearchable riches of Christ,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.3.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:9",
      "text": "and to make all men see what is the plan of the mystery hidden for ages in God who created all things;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.3.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:10",
      "text": "that through the church the manifold wisdom of God might now be made known to the principalities and powers in the heavenly places.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.3.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:11",
      "text": "This was according to the eternal purpose which he has realized in Christ Jesus our Lord,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.3.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:12",
      "text": "in whom we have boldness and confidence of access through our faith in him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.3.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:13",
      "text": "So I ask you not to lose heart over what I am suffering for you, which is your glory.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.3.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:14",
      "text": "For this reason I bow my knees before the Father,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.3.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:15",
      "text": "from whom every family in heaven and on earth is named,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.3.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:16",
      "text": "that according to the riches of his glory he may grant you to be strengthened with might through his Spirit in the inner man,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.3.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:17",
      "text": "and that Christ may dwell in your hearts through faith; that you, being rooted and grounded in love,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.3.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:18",
      "text": "may have power to comprehend with all the saints what is the breadth and length and height and depth,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.3.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:19",
      "text": "and to know the love of Christ which surpasses knowledge, that you may be filled with all the fulness of God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.3.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:20",
      "text": "Now to him who by the power at work within us is able to do far more abundantly than all that we ask or think,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.3.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:21",
      "text": "to him be glory in the church and in Christ Jesus to all generations, for ever and ever. Amen.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
